data.content:
• ON24 REST API
  • ››API Overview
  • ››Data Dictionary
  • ››Attendee

Attendee

Fields:

ON24 API Name

Description

Format

answeredpolls

The number of polls the Attendee responded to for this specific webinar. Note: All of the Attendee fields capture data for this specific webinar. It is not aggregated across all ON24 engagement.

Integer

answeredsurveys

Number of surveys the user responded to (not survey questions)

Integer

archivemediaplayerminutes

Total minutes of the media player from on-demand viewing sessions. The total minutes will be from the start of the media file to the maximum end time.For OD events, viewing at normal or fast speed should still count as minutes. Only valid if the "Prevent users from manually advancing during On Demand playback" is enabled.

Integer

archiveminutes

Total number of minutes an attendee viewed on-demand.

Integer

archiveviewed

Number of times the attendee launched the event console during the archive/on-demand period of the event.

Integer

askedquestions

Number of questions the user asked

Integer

attendancepartnerref

See the partnerref definition. The only difference is this value is in the attendee record, whereas partnerref is in the registrant record.

String

breakouts

ARRAY: Includes summary of breakout rooms attended - name, role and cumulative live minutes.
"breakoutid": "4816",
"breakoutname": "Breakout Room Sample",
"breakoutrole": "Attendee",
"breakoutcumulativeliveminutes": 15

String

campaigncode

The Salesforce campaign id (or any external identifier) that should have a 1:1 relationship with the ON24 eventid.

String

certificationcredit

ARRAY: Certification details - NR (no credits configured) or hours specified in Credit for Completion in certification widget. Date and time user successfully passed certification widget. ON24 system generated URL for an attendee's certificate via the certification widget within an ON24 Event. Results will come in the form - C= Certified, PC: Partially certified, NC: Not certified.
"certificationid": 83328985,
"certificationresult": "C",
"certificationname": "Certification 1",
"certificationcredit": "NR",
"certificationtimestamp": "2013-03-11T12:29:41-07:00",
"certificationurl": "https://event.on24.com/ceCertficate
/26/18/35/24/2/certificate_83328985.pdf"

 

clientid

ID of client account

Integer

contactus

ARRAY: Details on Take Action widgets clicked thru - name, type, action and submitted timestamp.
"widgetid": "7884",
"widgetname": "Contact us 1",
"widgettype": "contactus",
"widgetaction": "john.doe@on24.com",
"widgetsubmittedtimestamp": "2015-05-20T11:18:13-07:00"

String

contactuswidgetname

Contactus widget name

String

contactuswidgetsubmittedtimestamp

Contactus widget submitted time stamp

DateTime

contactuswidgettype

Contactus widget type

String

calltoactions

ARRAY: Details on Take Action widgets clicked thru - name, number of clicks, action and submitted timestamp.
"ctaid": "83970357",
"ctaname": "Call To Action 1",
"clicks": "3",
"action": "https://www.calltoactionurl.com",
"date": "2015-05-19T11:10:00-07:00"

 

cumulativearchiveminutes

Number of minutes the user attended the archived/on-demand portion of this event. Multiple console launches are aggregated into a single number.

Integer

cumulativeliveminutes

Number of minutes the user attended the live portion of this event. Multiple console launches are aggregated into a single number.

Integer

democonversions

ARRAY: Includes Demo Request widget details - name, type, action and submitted timestamp.
"widgetid": "98533852",
"widgetname": "Schedule a Demo Sample",
"widgettype": "request_a_demo",
"widgetaction": "jane.doe@on24.com",
"widgetsubmittedtimestamp": "2016-01-01T11:00:23-07:00"

 

drift

ARRAY: Includes Drift Conversations details - name, type, action and submitted timestamp.
"widgetid": "93858367",
"widgetname": "startConversation",
"widgettype": "drift",
"widgetaction": "Jan 01, 2016 10:00 AM",
"widgetsubmittedtimestamp": "2016-01-01T11:07:23-07:00"

 

email

The email address for this attendee.

String

engagementscore

This is a number between 0 and 10.0 measuring how engaged a user was based on activity during the event

Decimal

eventid

The unique ON24 event identifer found within the ON24 platform. We strongly recommend you name the eventid field "ON24_eventid". The field is required on the Campaign and Campaign Member objects.

Integer

eventtime

Published date and time of the event

DateTime

eventtitle

Title for the event

String

eventuserid

Unique user identifier auto-generated by ON24

Integer

exteventusercd

Hidden registration field typically used to store external platform IDs

String

firstarchiveactivity

Date and time attendee first opened the event console during the archived/on-demand event

DateTime

firstliveactivity

Date and time attendee first opened the event console during the live event

DateTime

freetrial

ARRAY: Includes Free trial widget details - name, type, action and submitted timestamp.
"widgetid": "93838564",
"widgetname": "Free Trial Sample",
"widgettype": "free_trial",
"widgetaction": "john.doe@on24.com",
"widgetsubmittedtimestamp": "2016-01-01T11:07:23-07:00"

 

getpricing

ARRAY: Includes Get Pricing widget details - name, type, action and submitted timestamp.
"widgetid": 7891,
"widgetname": "Price Quote 1",
"widgettype": "price_quote",
"widgetaction": "https://www.google.com/",
"widgetsubmittedtimestamp": "2015-05-20T02:29:30-07:00"

 

isblocked

Blocked from the webcast - Y or N

String

lastarchiveactivity

Date and time attendee last opened the event console during the archived/on-demand event

DateTime

lastliveactivity

Date and time attendee last opened the event console during the live event

DateTime

launchmode

Launched "At the venue" or "Remote"

String

liveminutes

Total number of minutes attendee viewed live, or real-time during the event.

Integer

livemediaplayerminutes

Total number of minutes that the media player was active for the live session.

Integer

liveviewed

Number of times the attendee launched the event console during the live event.

Integer

meetingconversions

ARRAY: Includes Meeting conversion widget details - name, type, action and submitted timestamp.
"widgetid": "98533828",
"widgetname": "Book a Meeting Sample",
"widgettype": "book_a_meeting",
"widgetaction": "https://www.bookedmeeting.com",
"widgetsubmittedtimestamp": "2016-01-01T10:00:23-07:00"

 

partnerref

To track the origin of the registrant/attendee. If you use multiple registration pages for the same webcast, you can include a Partner Referral code in the audience URL to track the individual sources. For example, you may promote an event through an email campaign or post it in Facebook. As a result, the registration URL may appear as below. However, the partnerref code value would be "email" or "facebook." ***NOTE: partnerref WILL work with links shortened into bit.ly links. The audience url with the partnerref can be shortened into bit.ly links. Do not append the partnerref to an existing bit.ly link.

○ https://event.on24.com/wcc/r/eventid/xxxx?partnerref=email
○ https://event.on24.com/wcc/r/eventid/xxxx?partnerref=facebook.

The value for the field would be "email" or "facebook." The value is in the registrant record, whereas the attendancepartnerref is in the attendee record.

The partnerref field is not updatable once the record is created.

String

polls

ARRAY: Poll Q&A for up to 10 questions. Client-determined poll question asked to the audience and the user-submitted answer to the poll.
"questionid": 1000697,
"createtimestamp": "2016-09-09T10:00:23-07:00",
"content": "Question 1",
"answer": {
"createtimestamp": "2016-09-09T10:05:23-07:00",
"content": "Properly Answered",
"presenterid": 2223110,
"presentername": "Brendan XXXXXX",
"privacy": "Private"

 

resources

ARRAY: Name of resource viewed in the Resource Widget with timestamp.
"resourceid": 30919784,
"resourceviewed": "Resources",
"resourceviewedtimestamp": "2016-09-09T13:46:20-07:00"

 

sourcecampaigncode

Campaign Code captured if registrant originated from Ehub

String

sourceeventid

Unique identifier used to determine if the source was Webcast Elite, Engagement Hub, Go Live, or Target. Say a registrant went into Engagement Hub and clicked on videos and content. The sourceeventid would reflect eHub. If someone registered for an Elite event, then the value would reflect the eventid.

Integer

surveys

ARRAY: Client-determined survey question asked to the audience and user-submitted answer to the survey question.
"surveyid": "1000607_survey1",
"surveysubmittedtimestamp": "2016-09-09T13:52:06-07:00",
"surveyquestions":[
{
"surveyquestionid": 987654,
"surveyquestion": "what is the number phi ?",

"questioncode": "110",
"surveyanswers":[
"It is the basis for the golden ratio: 1.618"
],
"surveyanswersdetail": [
{
"answercode": "choice1",
"answer": "It is the basis for the golden ratio: 1.618"
}

 

testwidgets

ARRAY: Values are P = Passed and F = Failed
"testwidgetresult": "P",
"retries": 0,
"correctanswersneeded": 2,
"correctanswersprovided": 2

 

testwidgetresult

Values are P = Passed and F = Failed

String

totalresourcesviewed

total number or resources viewed from the Resource Widget

Integer

twitterwidget

ARRAY: If a customer registers via a twitter (X) post
"date": "2015-05-19T11:02:39-07:00",
"tweetdescription": "A new Webinar on Artificial Intelligence has
been scheduled. Check www.on24.com/eventschedule"

 

questions

ARRAY: User submitted question through Q&A widget and the presenter response if answered.
"questionid": 1000697,
"createtimestamp": "2016-09-09T10:00:23-07:00",
"content": "Question 1",
"answer": {
"createtimestamp": "2016-09-09T10:05:23-07:00",
"content": "Properly Answered",
"presenterid": 2223110,
"presentername": "Brendan XXXXXX",
"privacy": "Private"

 

userprofileurl

The Prospect Engagement Profile URL for the attendee

String

userstatus

Active or Inactive

String

 

For Virtual Environment ONLY:

ON24 API Name

DESCRIPTION

Format

locationsvisited

Number of locations attendee visited.

Integer

locationvisits

ARRAY: Includes details on locations visited - code, name, sponsor name, number of times visited, duration of visit and cumulative duration.
"locationid": 2,
"locationcode": "home",
"locationname": "Plaza",
"sponsorid": 0,
"sponsorname": "Environment-level",
"visits": 31,
"visitsduration": 44,
"cumulativevisitsduration": 44
